casebody.data:
7 Cal.Rptr. 733] [Crim. No. 3760. First Dist., Div. Two. Sept. 20, 1960.] THE PEOPLE, Respondent, v. JACK M. HARRISON, Appellant.

A. L. Bjorklund, Jr., under appointment by the District Court of Appeal, for Appellant.

Stanley Mosk, Attorney General, Arlo E. Smith and Joseph I. Kelly, Deputy Attorneys General, for Respondent.

SHOEMAKER, J.

For the reasons stated in People v. Harrison, 182 Cal.App.2d 758 [6 Cal.Rptr. 345], the order denying appellant’s motion for new trial is affirmed.

Kaufman, P. J., and Draper, J., concurred.
